			<abstract>
				<p>Testimony of Abraham Peller regarding the fate of the Jews of Biecz under the German occupation, describing executions and liquidation of the ghetto in August 1942. In February 1942, the author survived an execution in which his family perished and he found shelter with Adela
					Jędrzejowska in Moszczenica.</p>
			</abstract>
