			<div type="transcription">
				<div type="original" xml:lang="pl">
					<!-- <p>Relacja <persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abrahama Pellera</persName> (sygn.
        301/1649)</p>
      <p>Oryginał, rękopis, 2 strony 210 x 295 mm, 1 strona 210 x 140 mm, język polski</p>-->
					<p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_01.jpg" n="1"/><persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName></p>
					<p>Urodzony w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764274/mszanka.html">Mszance</placeName> (powiat <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html">Gorlice</placeName>) <date when="1894">1894</date></p>
					<p>Zamieszkały w<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7533250/biecz.html"> Bieczu</placeName> koło <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasła</placeName>
						<note type="gloss">protokołowała</note>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_bauminger_roza">Róża Bauminger</persName></p>
					<p>Akcje w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7533250/biecz.html">Bieczu</placeName></p>
					<p>Z początku podczas okupacji było w naszym miasteczku spokojnie. <date when="1942-01-03">3 stycznia 1942</date> zaczęły się ekscesy. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Niemcy</term> wpadli do kilku mieszkań żydowskich i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastrzelili</term> 8 ludzi, którzy im przypadkowo wpadli w ręce. Nazwiska tych ludzi: dwaj bracia <persName ref="#ehri_et_heller">Heller</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bornstein"
							>Bornstein</persName> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łodzi</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_gilowa">Gilowa</persName> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łodzi</placeName>, <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">żona</term> krawca, matka trojga <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">dzieci</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_chaim">Chaim Itzinger</persName>
						z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">córką</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_regina">Reginą</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_czesniower_izak">Izak Cześniower</persName>. Był to tak zwany „kontyngent miastowy”. Podobne <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">mordy</term>
						miały miejsce w okolicznych miastach: w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html">Gorlicach</placeName> i innych. Jakaś <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles">Polka</term> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasła</placeName>
						doniosła, że <persName ref="#ehri_et_zucker">doktor Zucker</persName> z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasła</placeName> był komisarzem za czasów <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets">sowieckich</term>. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Zastrzelono</term> go z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">żoną</term> na miejscu, a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">córki</term> przywieziono do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecza</placeName>. Po drodze kazano im wysiąść i <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastrzelono</term> koło mojego domu. Mój <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">syn</term> pobiegł po <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">lekarza</term>, bo jedna z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">dziewcząt</term> żyła jeszcze, ale jej stan był beznadziejny i po pół godzinie <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">umarła</term>, a komendant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policji polskiej</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_fornalik_ignacy">Ignacy Fornalik</persName> doniósł na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policję</term>, że Żydzi ratowali <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
							type="subject">dziewczynę</term> skazaną na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">śmierć</term> i <date when="1942-02-16">16 lutego 1942</date>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">policjanci polscy</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-616" type="subject">zaaresztowali</term> tych <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">chłopców</term> i ich <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodziny</term>. Ja zostałem <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-616" type="subject">zaaresztowany</term> z <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">synem</term>. Szantażowali nas, by wyłudzić pieniądze. Otrzymali większą sumę, <persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielmana</persName> zwolnili od razu, mnie mieli wypuścić wieczorem, a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">chłopców</term> w nocy. W międzyczasie przyjechało <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">gestapo</orgName> i kazali sprowadzić z powrotem <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielmana</persName> z całą <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodziną</term>, a prócz tego <persName ref="#ehri_et_schnaps_hinda">Hindę Schnaps</persName> z dwoma <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">synami</term> i moją <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodzinę</term> złożoną z siedmiu osób. Skazańców skuwano po dwóch i o 7 wieczór wszystkich
							<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">rozstrzelono</term>. Byłem ostatni w kolei i patrzałem na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">śmierć</term> moich najbliższych. <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Zastrzelono</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielmana</persName>, do którego byłem przykuty. Zwalił się na ziemię, zalany krwią, <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_02.jpg" n="2"/> pociągnął mnie za sobą. Leżałem w kałuży krwi. <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject"
							>Niemcy</term> byli pewni, że <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">nie żyję</term>, lecz dla pewności <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">strzelili</term> mi w ramię. Następnie
						kazali uprzątnąć <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">trupy</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policjantom polskim</term>. Ci zdejmowali kajdanki z rąk <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">trupów</term>, a gdy przerwali robotę, skorzystałem z
						ich odejścia, podniosłem się i ociekając krwią zawlokłem się do okolicznej wsi, 20 kilometrów, do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenicy</placeName>, do chłopki <persName ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Adeli Jędrzejewskiej</persName>,
						która zachowała się bardzo ofiarnie i dała mi <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">schronienie</term>.</p>
					<p>Od naocznych świadków dowiedziałem się, że <date when="1942-02-18">18 lutego</date> zabrano 100 Żydów z <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecza</placeName>, przetrzymano 4 dni w <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669"
							type="subject">więzieniu</term>, odebrano im <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-660" type="subject">pieniądze</term>, a po 4-ch dniach <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">zastrzelono</term> 69-ciu
							(<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodzinę</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_schutzer">Schützer</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_gewurz">Gewürz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kleinman">Kleinman</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_wagschaller">Wagschaller</persName>). Okazało się, że <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policja polska</term> urządziła tę akcję na własną rękę i gdy przyszedł telefon od <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">gestapo</orgName> z <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasła</placeName>, zdołali już <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">uśmiercić</term> 31 ofiar. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject"
							>Policja polska</term> szantażowała ludność żydowską i wyłudzili 250 tysięcy złotych, w przeciwnym razie grozili podobną akcją. W kilka miesięcy później <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans">Niemcy</term> zabrali 14 Żydów rzekomo za to, że ich bracia byli <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1009" type="subject">komunistami</term> i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">rozstrzelali</term>. Nazwiska ofiar: <persName ref="#ehri_et_schneider"
						>Schneider</persName>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">rodzina</term> z 5-ciu osób, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kurz">Kurz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_jakobowicz">Jakóbowicz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_wagschal"
							>Wagschal</persName> z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">żoną</term>.</p>
					<p><date when="1942-08">W sierpniu 1942</date> nastąpiła <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject">akcja likwidacyjna</term>. <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">Zastrzelono</term> na miejscu
						170 ofiar i <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-748" type="subject">pochowano</term> na <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-747" type="subject">cmentarzu</term> żydowskim 700 ludzi załadowano do <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">wagonów</term> i wysłano do <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżca</placeName>. Tych, którzy się <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">ukryli</term>, wyłapywała <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">polska policja</term> i oddała w ręce <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">gestapo</orgName>. <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_03.jpg" n="3"/> Ja z <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">bratem</term> i 2-ma Żydami byliśmy <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">ukryci</term> u <persName ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Jędrzejewskiej</persName>. W tej wiosce <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">ukrywało
							się</term> jeszcze około 70 Żydów. Komendant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">policji polskiej</term> w tej wiosce, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> dostał rozkaz urządzenia obławy na Żydów <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">ukrywających się</term> w okolicy. Dał nam znać o grożącym nam niebezpieczeństwie i opuściliśmy <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenicę</placeName>, a
						nazajutrz zebrał 70-ciu chłopów i kazał im z widłami szukać Żydów po strychach. Oczywiście nie znaleźli ani jednego Żyda. <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> kilka razy <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-297" type="subject">uratował
							Żydów</term> z narażeniem własnego życia. Szantażowano go i komisarz <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">polskiej policji</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_kazmierczak">Kaźmierczak</persName> oddalił go z tej wsi (<placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765673/luzna.html">Łużna</placeName>) i przeniesiono go do <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasła</placeName>. Obecnie <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> jest burmistrzem w <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7534761/blazejow.html">Blasdorf</placeName><note type="gloss">Blasdorf bei Schömberg, obecnie - Błażejów</note> koło <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/3096779/kamienna-gora.html">Kamiennej Góry</placeName>.</p>
					<p><note type="gloss">podpis</note>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Peller Abraham</persName></p>
				</div>
				<div type="translation" xml:lang="en">
					<!--<p><persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName> Testimony (doc.
        301/1649)</p>
      <p>Original, manuscript, 2 pages 210 x 295 mm, 1 page 210 x 140 mm, Polish language.</p>-->
					<p><pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_01.jpg" n="1"/>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName></p>
					<p>Born at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764274/mszanka.html">Mszanka</placeName> (the <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html">Gorlice</placeName> county) in <date when="1894">1894</date></p>
					<p>Residing at <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>, near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> [recorded by] <persName ref="#ehri_et_bauminger_roza">[Róża] Bauminger</persName></p>
					<p>Actions in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName></p>
					<p>In the early days of the occupation it was quiet in our town. But on <date when="1942-01-03">January 3, 1942</date>, the excesses began. The <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> raided several Jewish homes and <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> 8 people who happened to fall into their hands. The names of these people are: two <persName ref="#ehri_et_heller">Heller</persName> brothers, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bornstein"
							>Bornstein</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_gilowa">Gilowa</persName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3093133/lodz.html">Łódź</placeName>, a <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term> of a tailor and mother of three <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-824" type="subject">children</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_chaim">Chaim
							Itzinger</persName> with his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">daughter</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_itzinger_regina">Regina</persName>, and <persName ref="#ehri_et_czesniower_izak">Izak Cześniower</persName>. It was the so-called <q>town quota</q>. Similar acts of <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
							>homicide</term> took place in the nearby towns: in <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/771804/gorlice.html">Gorlice</placeName>, and others. Some <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles" type="subject">Polish</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> informed that <persName ref="#ehri_et_zucker">Dr Zucker</persName> of <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName> had been a commissar during the times of the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_soviets" type="subject">Soviets</term>. He and his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825"
							type="subject">wife</term> were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> on the spot, and their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">daughters</term> were taken to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>. They were ordered to get out of the car and were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> near my house. My <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">son</term> ran to fetch a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-287" type="subject">doctor</term> because one of the <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girls</term> was still alive, but her state was hopeless, and she <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">died</term> half an hour later. <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_fornalik_ignacy">Ignacy Fornalik</persName>, commandant of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term>, informed the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119"
							type="subject">police</term> that some Jews had tried to save a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">girl</term> who had been sentenced to <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
							>death</term>, and on <date when="1942-02-16">February 16, 1942</date>, <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish policemen</term>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term> these <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">boys</term> and their <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819"
							type="subject">families</term>. My <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">son</term> and I were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-598" type="subject">arrested</term>, too. They blackmailed us to
						swindle us out of money, and they got a pretty large sum. <persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName> was freed immediately, I was to be released in the evening, and the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">boys</term> at
						night. But in the meantime the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> arrived, and they ordered to have <persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName> and his entire <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> brought back, and apart from them also <persName ref="#ehri_et_schnaps_hinda">Hinda Schnaps</persName> with her two <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826"
							type="subject">sons</term> and my entire <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> of seven. All of us were handcuffed in pairs, and at 7 pm everybody was <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term>. I was at the very rear, and looked at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">death</term> of my <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term>. Then they <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term>
						<persName ref="#ehri_et_spielman">Spielman</persName>, who was handcuffed with me. He tumbled down, all covered with blood, <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_02.jpg" n="2"/> and I fell with him. I was lying in a puddle of blood, and the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans"
							type="subject">Germans</term> thought that I was <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">dead</term>, but they shot me in the arm just to make sure. Then they ordered <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish policemen</term> to take the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-515" type="subject">bodies</term> away. They removed our handcuffs, and when they went away for a
						break, I took advantage of their absence, raised myself and, dripping blood, managed to drag myself to the village of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenica</placeName>, 20 kilometres away, to a <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_poles"
							type="subject">Polish</term> peasant <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">woman</term>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Adela Jędrzejewska</persName>, who was very generous towards me and gave me <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-265" type="subject">shelter</term>.</p>
					<p>I learnt from eye-witnesses that on <date when="1942-02-18">February 18</date>, 100 Jews were taken from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/776053/biecz.html">Biecz</placeName>. They were kept in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-669"
							type="subject">prison</term> for 4 days, their money was confiscated, and after 4 days 69 of them were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">shot</term> (the <persName ref="#ehri_et_schutzer">Schützer</persName>, <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_gewurz">Gewürz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kleinman">Kleinman</persName> and <persName ref="#ehri_et_wagschaller">Wagschaller</persName>
						<term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">families</term>). It turned out that the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> was responsible for organising this action, and
						when they got a phone call from the <orgName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName> from <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName>, they had already <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject">killed</term> 31 people. The <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> blackmailed the Jews and they swindled 250 thousand zlotys out
						of them, saying that if they didn’t pay, another similar action would be carried out. A few months later the <term ref="#ehri_et_nationalities_germans" type="subject">Germans</term> took and <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-745" type="subject"
							>shot</term> 14 other Jews. Allegedly, the charge against them was was that their brothers were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1000" type="subject">communists</term>. The names of some of the victims are: <persName ref="#ehri_et_schneider"
							>Schneider</persName>, a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-819" type="subject">family</term> of five, <persName ref="#ehri_et_kurz">Kurz</persName>, <persName ref="#ehri_et_jakobowicz">Jakóbowicz</persName>, and <persName
							ref="#ehri_et_wagschal">Wagschal</persName> with his <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-825" type="subject">wife</term>.</p>
					<p>In <date when="1942-08">August 1942</date> a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-551" type="subject">liquidation</term> action took place. 170 people were <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-541" type="subject">shot</term> on
						the spot and buried at the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-750" type="subject">Jewish cemetery</term>. 700 people were loaded onto <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-522" type="subject">cattle cars</term> and <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-115" type="subject">transported</term> to <placeName ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_camps-41" type="camp">Bełżec</placeName>. Those who managed to <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hide</term> were hunted down by the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> and turned over to the <orgName
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/authorities/ehri_cb-350">Gestapo</orgName>. <pb facs="EHRI-ET-ZIH3011649_03.jpg" n="3"/> I and my <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-826" type="subject">brother</term> and two other Jews were <term
							ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term> at <persName ref="#ehri_et_jedrzejewska_adela">Jędrzejewska’s</persName> home, and around 70 other Jews were in <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262"
							type="subject">hiding</term> in the same village. The commandant of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> in that village, <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName>, was ordered to conduct a
						search for the Jews <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-262" type="subject">hiding</term> in the area. He warned us against the danger we were in, and we left <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/764343/moszczenica.html">Moszczenica</placeName>.
						On the following day, he assembled 70 peasants with pitchforks, and ordered them to look for Jews in the attics. They certainly failed to find a single Jew. <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> risked his life several times to save Jews. He was blackmailed, and
						then removed by the commissar of the <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1119" type="subject">Polish police</term> from that particular village (of <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/765673/luzna.html">Łużna</placeName>) to <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/770293/jaslo.html">Jasło</placeName>. At present <persName ref="#ehri_et_bednarz">Bednarz</persName> is a <term ref="https://portal.ehri-project.eu/keywords/ehri_terms-1006" type="subject">mayor</term> in <placeName
							ref="http://www.geonames.org/7534761/blazejow.html">Blasdorf</placeName>
						<note type="gloss">Blasdorf bei Schömberg, Polish name: <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/7534761/blazejow.html">Błażejów</placeName>.</note> near <placeName ref="http://www.geonames.org/3096779/kamienna-gora.html">Kamienna Góra</placeName>.</p>
					<p>[signed by] <persName ref="#ehri_et_peller_abraham">Abraham Peller</persName></p>
